    "The two extremities of this gigantic parallelogram were occupied, the one by the famous marble table, so long, so broad, and so thick that, as the ancient land rolls--in a style that would have given Gargantua an appetite--say, \"such a slice of marble as was never beheld in the world\"; the other by the chapel where Louis XI.--*Paris*",
