    "It was covered with green silk, and bore in its centre a large piece of green glass, in imitation of an emerald.--*Paris*",
    "Gringoire was on the point of taking the bag in his hand.--*Paris*",
    "She drew back.--*Paris*",
    "The poet's curiosity was more and more aroused.--*Paris*",
    "She laid one finger on her mouth and concealed the amulet in her bosom.--*Paris*",
    "He tried a few more questions, but she hardly replied.--*Paris*",
    "She began to sing, to an ancient air,-- ~Mon p\u00e8re est oiseau, Ma m\u00e8re est oiselle.--*Paris*",
    "B Je passe l'eau sans nacelle, Je passe l'eau sans bateau, Ma m\u00e8re est oiselle, Mon p\u00e8re est oiseau~.--*Paris*",
    "She retired into her laconics again.--*Paris*",
    "She made her customary pretty grimace.--*Paris*",
    "Gringoire ceased, awaiting the effect of his harangue on the young girl.--*Paris*",
