    "At the first glance one read arrogance on his visage; at the second, craft.--*Paris*",
    "He was standing bareheaded, a long roll of parchment in his hand, behind the arm-chair in which was seated, his body ungracefully doubled up, his knees crossed, his elbow on the table, a very badly accoutred personage.--*Paris*",
