    "It was Louis XI.--*Paris*",
    "At some distance behind them, two men dressed in garments of Flemish style were conversing, who were not sufficiently lost in the shadow to prevent any one who had been present at the performance of Gringoire's mystery from recognizing in them two of the principal Flemish envoys, Guillaume Rym, the sagacious pensioner of Ghent, and Jacques Coppenole, the popular hosier.--*Paris*",
    "The reader will remember that these men were mixed up in the secret politics of Louis XI.--*Paris*",
