    "She set her daughter (down for she was still carrying her), in one corner of the cell which was not visible from without.--*Paris*",
    "She made her crouch down, arranged her carefully so that neither foot nor hand projected from the shadow, untied her black hair which she spread over her white robe to conceal it, placed in front of her her jug and her paving stone, the only articles of furniture which she possessed, imagining that this jug and stone would hide her.--*Paris*",
    "And when this was finished she became more tranquil, and knelt down to pray.--*Paris*",
