    "At length he shook his head and leaped into his saddle.--*Paris*",
    "Gudule's horribly compressed heart now dilated, and she said in a low voice, as she cast a glance at her daughter, whom she had not ventured to look at while they were there, \"Saved!\"--*Paris*",
    "The poor child had remained all this time in her corner, without breathing, without moving, with the idea of death before her.--*Paris*",
    "She had lost nothing of the scene between Gudule and Tristan, and the anguish of her mother had found its echo in her heart.--*Paris*",
    "She had heard all the successive snappings of the thread by which she hung suspended over the gulf; twenty times she had fancied that she saw it break, and at last she began to breathe again and to feel her foot on firm ground.--*Paris*",
